<TEXT>
gradually now comes the hurt to the children of chernobyl as 
the silent hidden blight starts appearing theyre beginning to 
get help from scattered groups of american christians 
the situation is bad and its going to get worse said the 
rev paul s moore whose new york city radio ministry citihope 
is raising money for medical supplies 
in a real way it means giving children back their lives he 
said 
a threatening shadow fell over inhabitants of the ukraine and 
byelorussia after the fiery rupture of a soviet nuclear plant on 
april 26 1986 at chernobyl filled the atmosphere with radioactive 
particles 
but only lately has the extent of the effects of that accident 
begun to appear with the impact increasing with time 
pyotr k kravchanka foreign affairs minister of the 
byelorussian republic on which 70 percent of the contamination 
settled said that at the outset the resulting volume of cancer and 
related cases could not be predicted 
we are now seeing only the beginning stage he said in an 
interview citing a doubling of thyroid ailments among children a 
sevenfold increase in anemia cases and a rise in leukemia cases 
the peak volume of sickness has not yet come he said 
scientists project the mounting toll will hit its high point in 
199697 he said but treatment is severely limited by a lack of 
medicine and diagnostic equipment 
a fifth of byelorussias population or 22 million people 
including 800000 children have become innocent victims of 
chernobyl the hostages of postponed effects of radiation he 
told the united nations general assembly 
as the disasters effects grow several small independent 
american religious and other groups as well as ethnic communities 
of byelorussians and ukrainians in some cities have begun limited 
steps to provide medical aid 
a catalyzing influence for such efforts resulted from moores 
visit in september to minsk capital of byelorussia where he 
observed firsthand the spreading marks of radiation to which 
children are most vulnerable 
you cant realize the gravity of it until you experience it 
until flesh touches your flesh and you go through the hospitals 
with the doctors and see the wasting bodies of the children he 
said most americans are not aware of the extent of the 
implications now and in the future 
he said he was told 37000 byelorussian children are being 
treated for precancerous conditions with more cases diagnosed 
daily but he added the supply of medicine is so inadequate that 
only 15 percent can be saved compared to the 85 percent who could 
be saved with sufficient medicine 
soviet pharmaceutical supplies limited and chiefly from east 
germany were said to have been disrupted by german reunification 
moore also an assistant minister at st georges church in 
manhattan said that through sponsorships enlisted on his radio 
ministry his project so far has supplied 650000 worth of 
methotrexate and other anticancer drugs and vitamins 
he said that as a result treatment has been started on 400 
byelorussian children and that by early january he expects to 
have rounded up enough medicine to increase that number to 1000 
moore said pharmaceutical companies will provide the drugs for 
such charitable purposes at 5 percent of costs meaning that the 
usual cost of 4000 to 5000 for two or three years of treatment 
to bring a cancerous condition into remission is reduced to 100 to 
200 per child 
the rev michael christensen of san franciscos hamilton united 
methodist church is coordinator of moores expanding project 
paul maxey associate executive director of interchurch medical 
assistance of new windsor md which serves 15 relief agencies as 
a liaison with drug companies in obtaining medicines for such 
causes said 
reaction to the chernobyl situation has been slow because of 
the incubation time before the effects show up churches have not 
been challenged to do much about it but it has now become a very 
distressing problem 
he said a few mostly local groups now are getting involved 
in richmond va the rev paul f mccleary director of the 
christian childrens fund said his group began sending aid to the 
soviets as a result of a factfinding trip with a virginia medical 
team to minsk in midnovember 
its a very grave situation he said adding that a 
prechristmas shipment of medicine was being assembled 
its a very large medical catastrophe and assistance is needed 
to improve the diagnosis process and start treatment earlier he 
said 
its the first instance of a major nuclear catastrophe 
something entirely new in the human experience its important that 
we monitor it and track the record so if another such event occurs 
we cope with it more properly 
its a very significant activity for us and all mankind 
