<TEXT>
highlights of foreign minister eduard 
shevardnadzes career 
nearly completed negotiations on the strategic arms reduction 
treaty to slash superpower longrange nuclear arsenals by up to 
half president mikhail s gorbachev and president bush are 
expected to sign the pact at a february summit in moscow 
negotiated withdrawal of soviet forces from afghanistan in 1989 
and admitted that the soviet incursion there was a mistake 
completed agreement on the reduction of warsaw pact and nato 
conventional forces in europe signed in 1990 
completed agreement to eliminate us and soviet mediumrange 
nuclear missiles signed in 1987 
acknowledged that the krasnoyarsk phasedarray radar 
emplacement violated the 1972 antiballistic missile treaty 
oversaw the freeing of east bloc countries in europe in 
198990 including the fall of the berlin wall and the 
reunification of germany 
took part in the mediation of the civil war in southern africa 
leading to independence for namibia and the withdrawal of cuban 
forces from angola in 1989 
helped end a 30year estrangement with china in 1989 
oversaw the restoration of diplomatic relations with albania 
and saudi arabia in 1990 
oversaw the improvement of relations with israel leading to 
the reestablishment of consular ties in 1990 
oversaw the normalization of relations with south korea and the 
vatican in 1990 
established in 1988 the longrange goal of withdrawing all 
soviet troops to within soviet borders 
helped forge the closest ussoviet ties since world war ii 
with an unprecedented 19 meetings with secretary of state james a 
baker iii in 1990 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

