<DOCNO> AP901221-0014 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
eduard a shevardnadze helped create a new era in 
soviet foreign policy marked by sweeping arms control agreements 
withdrawal from afghanistan and the collapse of communist regimes 
in eastern europe 
shevardnadze who announced thursday he would resign as foreign 
minister was a novice in international affairs when he was chosen 
by mikhail s gorbachev for the highprofile job in july 1985 
he had spent most of his political career working for as a 
communist party functionary 
diplomats and soviet watchers rushed to find out more about him 
he was fairly wellknown within the soviet union for battling crime 
and corruption in his native georgia where was in charge of the 
interior ministry and the police shevardnadze replaced the dour 
andrei a gromyko who was foreign minister for 28 years and was 
known as mr nyet for his tough negotiating stands 
the genial whitehaired shevardnadze quickly reversed gears 
implementing gorbachevs new thinking and promoting a less 
aggressive foreign policy aimed at lessening world tensions 
hardworking wellbriefed and quick to learn shevardnadze 
developed good working relations with his western counterparts and 
often warm personal relations 
it was gorbachev who won the nobel peace prize this year but it 
was the 62yearold shevardnadze who did much of the leg work 
former foreign ministry spokesman gennady gerasimov referred to his 
globetrotting boss as the flying georgian 
like gorbachev shevardnadze is a pragmatist rather than an 
oldstyle hardline communist gorbachev recently credited 
shevardnadze a friend dating back to their teens with helping 
develop the concept of perestroika during a walk along a beach in 
march 1985 
we were walking and talking gorbachev told the communist 
party newspaper pravda we compared notes he said that 
everything was rotten through 
it was not easy for us to reach those conclusions gorbachev 
said we had seen a lot especially considering that we had seen 
the war so we had seen a lot and knew a lot 
together gorbachev and shevardnadze closed the final chapter in 
the cold war permitting the unification of germany and the return 
of democracy to eastern europe and improving relations with the 
united states 
they moved to heal rifts with japan south korea and isreal and 
cooled relations with hardline regimes such as cuba and north 
korea 
when iraq invaded kuwait on aug 2 the soviet union was among 
the first to condemn its longtime ally iraq and call for 
unconditional withdrawal in an unprecedented display of superpower 
cooperation moscow has backed all un resolutions aimed at 
dislodging the iraqi forces 
shevardnadze made a real era in our international policies 
sergei stankevich moscows deputy mayor said in tribute thursday 
shevardnadze a teachers son was born in the village of mamati 
near the black sea on jan 25 1928 he rose through the ranks of 
the communist youth league and the georgian communist party 
became the republics interior minister in 1965 and its party 
leader in 1972 
georgia had a reputation for corruption and as interior minister 
shevardnadze gained national attention for his key role in one of 
the republics most infamous examples of nepotism and bribery 
the case involved otari lazishvili who used a personal 
friendship with a former soviet general prosecutor to protect 
numerous illegal economic dealings 
shevardnadze gradually and successfully moved against lazishvili 
in 1972 he was then made party boss and continued the crackdown 
in his book russia author robert kaiser tells how 
shevardnadze tested his own regulations against exporting georgian 
produce he filled a car trunk with tomatoes dressed in peasant 
clothes and drove north toward the russian border bribing border 
guards en route a purge of the border patrol ensued 
shevardnadze also pioneered the use of public opinion polls in 
the soviet union creating in 1966 an institute for the study of 
public opnion to provide reliable data about the extent of crime 
and corruption 
he promoted economic reform long before perestroika was a 
household word allowing some georgian enterprises such as 
restaurants to adopt elements of private enterprise 
in 1978 shevardnadze was appointed a nonvoting member of the 
national communist party politburo which until recent reforms 
wielded immense power over the government of the country as well as 
the party in 1985 after gorbachev took over leadership of the 
communist party shevardnadze was made a full member 
shevardnades wife nanuli is a former journalist 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

