<TEXT>
more than 1 million iraqis fled their homes 
in the capital today in a major evacuation drill to test the 
populations readiness in the event of war in the persian gulf 
the civil defense exercise got under way on schedule at 7 am 
with air raid sirens blaring across the eastern part of baghdad 
which is divided by the tigris river 
the drill was expected to involve nearly 2 million people but 
residents said nearly half stayed home 
iraqi preparations for war have increased since the un 
security council late last month authorized military force to drive 
the iraqi army from kuwait if it does not leave the conquered 
emirate by jan 15 
with the first siren today families began pouring into the 
streets some ran to civil defense centers set up by the government 
and others jumped into their cars and sped away 
hundreds of buses waiting at the civil defense centers took 
evacuees to points about 10 miles to the north east and south of 
the city 
the evacuees carried blankets food and personal documents 
the drill was expected to last all day 
on thursday basra iraqs secondlargest city and the closest 
to the border with occupied kuwait was evacuated in a similar 
exercise residents there said almost the entire population of 1 
million people participated in that drill 
among other war preparations in the past couple of weeks there 
have been instructions to build bomb shelters throughout the 
capital and courses in civil defense and firstaid are being 
pushed by the government 
government officials have been instructing the population in 
public announcements to leave their houses carefully locked during 
the evacuation drills police cars were to patrol the city to 
protect private property 
businesses and all government offices were closed today the 
moslem sabbath so the exercise did not affect commerce 
on saturday the western part of the city is to be evacuated in 
similar drills the population also about 2 million will be moved 
north west and south of the city 
government offices also were expected to be closed on saturday 
for the drills 
</TEXT>
