the official said joseph c wilson iv the chief us diplomat 
in baghdad received a telephone cll from the state department in 
washington after the first missile was fired 
the call reportedly informed him that the balloon is going up 
this is no drill later officials reported the launch was a 
test 
the times said the missiles were launched from a site near 
basra in southeastern iraq and traveled more than 400 miles west 
