authority and the capability to effect the reductions in the army 
without creating a backlash from angry sandinistas guzman said 
the sandinistas who ruled the country from 1979 until their 
defeat in last februarys elections still command a mass movement 
capable of bringing the country to its knees with strikes they 
also have most of the guns and bullets 
but mrs chamorro also agreed to reduce the armed forces now 
numbering 28434 troops to about 16000 over the coming years 
guzman said 
the military had 100000 men and women under arms when she came 
to power april 25 once the largest force in central america the 
sandinista peoples army is now the fourth biggest after those of 
el salvador honduras and guatemala 
the armys budget was 190 million this year the last budget 
the sandinista government approved and military officials 
presented a 1991 budget proposal of 160 million 
