<TEXT>
a strong earthquake early today shook 
greece bulgaria yugoslavia and romania killing one person 
injuring at least 15 people and damaging buildings authorities 
said 
the salonica seismological institute said the temblor measured 
55 on the richter scale and was centered in the village of 
goumenisa about 35 miles northwest of the aegean coastal city of 
salonica the spokesman vasillis papazachos said the temblor was 
followed by several smaller aftershocks 
pat jorgenson of the us geological survey in menlo park 
calif said the quake measured 61 on the richter scale 
it was also felt in yugoslavia bulgaria and romania news 
reports said 
a police spokesman in the greek town of edessa 20 miles west of 
the epicenter said a 60yearold woman was killed there 
she was crushed when a wall collapsed on her the rest of the 
house remained standing said the spokesman who spoke on 
condition of anonymity 
he said 10 people were treated and released from edessa 
hospital while two others remained hospitalized 
many houses in edessa suffered minor damage and two apartment 
buildings were near collapse said the spokesman 
a police spokesman at regional headquarters in salonica said 
three people suffered slight injuries in goumenisa and three houses 
collapsed he said telephone communications with the town were 
disrupted 
he said the temblor was felt throughout northern greece and 
lasted about 20 seconds people here in salonica were rushing out 
of their buildings in panic 
the quake caused minor injuries and damaged houses in southern 
yugoslavia the tanjug news agency reported the quake forced the 
interruption of classes at schools in the southern yugoslav 
republic of macedonia tanjug said 
no injuries or damage were reported in bulgaria and romania 
northern greece is a seismologically active region an 
earthquake measuring 65 on the richter scale struck salonica in 
1978 killing 40 people 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on a 
seismograph 
a magnitude 5 quake can cause considerable damage while a 6 
reading can cause severe damage in populated areas 
