defense lawyer j ross haffey said he expected to appeal the 
verdicts after a jan 7 hearing in which jurors decide whether luff 
should be put to death luff had pleaded innocent by reason of 
insanity 
lundgren a defrocked lay minister of the reorganized church of 
jesus christ of latter day saints has admitted to firing the shots 
that killed the family he said scriptures told him to kill the 
family members because they were sinners he has been sentenced to 
death 
although lundgren killed the averys luff was a willing 
participant prosecutors said lundgren had told luff and other 
cult members that the averys had to die before the cult could go on 
a wilderness outing to see god 
luff has testified that he thought lundgren was a prophet who 
was going to lead his family to zion a place where man and god 
could live in peace 
testimony indicated that luff helped dig a pit and gather rocks 
that would be thrown on top of the averys bodies to keep them from 
rising in the barns soft dirt 
