the catholic archdiocese of atlanta said it wont 
seek to recover more than 20000 in church funds that went to a 
woman whose affair with the nations highestranking black catholic 
led to his resignation 
an audit of the archdiocese and two parishes conducted by a 
public accounting firm revealed thursday that about 5835 from 
the individual churches went directly to vicki long or to her 
creditors to pay her rent utilities or charge cards 
the archdiocese paid 14556 in medical expenses for ms long 
through the summer of 1990 but the audit said no archdiocese funds 
went directly to her 
the archdiocese initiated the audit after the resignations last 
summer of archbishop eugene marino and the rev michael woods a 
sandy springs priest who said he had a sexual relationship with ms 
long 
ms long denied the relationship with woods but claimed she was 
married to marino and filed a paternity suit in 1987 against 
another priest the rev donal keohane of columbus a blood test 
later showed keohane did not father her daughter 
