allegheny river today in search of a sunken barge that paralyzed 
part of the nations busiest inland port for a third day 
a fourmile stretch of the rainswollen river was closed 
wednesday and thursday from point state park in downtown pittsburgh 
northeast to the highland park bridge coast guard lt cmdr rhea 
giacoma said 
one little barge like this is more of a nuisance than anything 
else said john reed spokesman for the us army corps of 
