southern yugoslavia republic of macedonia on the border with 
greece the tanjug news agency reported 
there were no reports of damage or injuries in romania and 
bulgaria 
a spokesman at the salonica institute said the temblor seems 
to have been the main quake although we are gathering data to make 
sure it was not a foreshock 
an earthquake measuring 65 on the richter scale struck salonica 
in 1978 killing 40 people a temblor measuring 58 on the richter 
scale preceded it by less than a month 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on a 
seismograph a quake measuring 50 can cause considerable damage 
and one measuring 60 can cause severe damage in populated areas 
