camel off the back said lt col henry wyatt a spokesman for 
the defense logistics agency which oversees the shipments he said 
it was expected to take about a week 
the magazine publisher who organized the shipment said he was 
vexed by the delay 
its magazines that were sending were not sending 
cigarettes said tim karnes publisher of auction guide and the 
organizer of operation desert news 
karnes said the magazines which include life fine woodworking 
and modern drummer were donated to the organization by the 
publishers 
everybody involved knew that rj reynolds was the sponsor 
karnes added 
all the magazines some of which contain cigarette advertising 
were approved by the defense department he said the covers were 
printed wednesday at quebecor printing usa in st cloud minn 
i dont think the advertisement about cigarettes should 
jeopardize the ability to provide this reading material which is 
just desperately needed for morale karnes said in a telephone 
interview from acapulco mexico where he was vacationing 
reynolds is the organizations only corporate sponsor so far 
although karnes said the group was seeking others 
karnes said the organization submitted a rough draft of the 
