the croatian parliament adopted a new 
constitution friday that would give the countrys secondlargest 
republic the right to secede media reports said 
the move is likely to worsen the traditionally tense relations 
between croatians and minority serbs in the republic 
the new constitution follows an electoral victory last spring by 
the centerright government over communists who had been ruling the 
republic 
the new document provides for croatia to secede from yugoslavia 
if twothirds of the legislature votes for such a proposal the 
reports said 
they said a statewide plebiscite would then have to be held if 
a simple majority of the electorate votes in favor of secession 
the motion would be upheld 
fridays vote was preceded by an acrimonious debate over 
minority rights between ethnic serbian and croatian deputies in the 
legislature the national tanjug news agency reported 
it said that 16 deputies representing croatias 500000member 
serbian minority walked out of the parliamentary session before the 
