the smallest city in this countrys 
smallest state is in danger of dying and needs a transfusion of 
state funds to survive a commission reviewing the communitys 
financial health said friday 
even if the state of rhode island takes financial responsibility 
for the schools of central falls this gritty mill city of 17000 
could expire members of a state review commission said 
the clock is ticking we dont have much time if you have a 
heart problem and you dont get a transplant whats the 
alternative asked james mahoney vice chairman of the central 
falls review commission 
the city named for the blackstone river falls that powered the 
