amtrak spokesman john jacobsen said sometimes it just separates 
the rails but whether it actually cracks a rail or simply 
separates a rail you cant operate a train you have to wait to 
get a repair crew there 
between 40 and 50 families in pocatello idaho were evacuated 
from their homes when overnight temperatures that dipped to 
17below created ice jams that caused the nearby portneuf river to 
rise more than four feet in two hours 
more than 3000 homes in southern oregon lost their natural gas 
supply when pressure dropped in a pipeline that supplies the area 
gas company officials said it could take days to restore gas to all 
the households 
the cold also apparently caused a water valve to rupture in the 
ogden utah city mall friday sending icy water pouring into as 
many as 20 stores 
thunderstorms and twisters swirled through mississippi and 
louisiana afternoon overturning a tractortrailer rig blowing 
cars off the road damaging buildings and injuring at least five 
people 
the cold caused power outages in jackson hole wyo and in 
arlee st ignatius and ravalli mont 
the outages kept the jackson hole ski resort from opening but 
in general the storm was a boon to the ski industry in the rockies 
and the sierra nevada 
and while subzero temperatures whipping winds and blowing snow 
made life a little harder for some people others took it in 
stride 
this is how its supposed to be said kathy walters of west 
des moines iowa as she prepared to go out into the 33below wind 
chill its christmas first comes ice then snow 
