homosexuality remains illegal in the soviet union 
after five years of political reform and attempts to start a gay 
liberation movement have been denounced by the press with a venom 
reminiscent of another era 
religion pornography gambling and political freethinking once 
grievous sins against communist society flourish under president 
mikhail s gorbachev but homosexuality has stayed underground one 
of the last taboos 
in the past year a few dozen soviet gays and lesbians have 
begun a campaign to get homosexuality legalized and increase social 
tolerance 
they have achieved some successes including launching the 
countrys first homosexual newspaper but soviet homosexuals say 
they also have been beaten by youth gangs in recent months and 
forced by police to undergo blood tests for aids 
there is no real gay liberation movement here and i am very 
skeptical there will be one said dmitri 33 a scientist like 
other homosexuals interviewed he asked to be identified only by 
his first name 
i am absolutely sure that if they announced a rally few 
people would turn out he said i personally wouldnt they 
would photograph us and that could lead to problems at work maybe 
even getting fired 
