years for homosexual acts between consenting adults and all the 
cases were in provincial towns 
there is no reason to believe homosexuality is any less common 
in the soviet union than anywhere else on earth said vladimir 
shakhidshanian it just meets less public acceptance here 
shakhidshanian 50 is the author of a forthcoming book about 
sex called 1001 questions about that the avuncular armenian 
dispenses advice about sex in newspapers and on television 
during an interview in his cluttered office he riffled through 
some of the 8000 letters he has received from viewers including 
many gays and lesbians 
soviet homosexuals suffer loneliness shame and discomfort in 
their private lives and ignorance prejudice and persecution in 
society he said 
he said he knew of no soviet polls on attitudes toward 
homosexuality shakhidshanian said his letters and interviews 
indicated that tolerance of homosexuality rose in the early 1980s 
under western influence 
then came aids he said and turned public opinion 
strongly against homosexuals again 
according to official statistics 565 soviet citizens including 
74 homosexuals are infected with hiv the aids virus 
the leading causes of the spread of aids in the soviet union are 
medical mistakes including reuse of infected syringes and 
heterosexual relations said irina yeremova an epidemiologist 
homosexuals often are blamed she said 
the law against homosexuality dating from the 1930s sometimes 
has been used for political purposes as in the case of the late 
sergei paradzhanov an armenian film maker imprisoned in 197278 
he was convicted of homosexuality but his real crime was signing a 
ltter demanding the release of ukrainian dissidents 
anatoly sobchak a former law professor who now is mayor of 
leningrad and a member of the national legislature said he 
believes the statute will be removed when a new criminal code is 
adopted in 1991 
technically it prohibits only male homosexuality not 
lesbianism but lesbians are active in the nascent homosexual 
rights movement 
we suffer from the same kind of social intolerance the same 
fear of being fired under some pretext the same desire to live 
freely said mila 33 
the movements leading organization formed in moscow in october 
1989 is the association of sexuality minorities which publishes 
tema or theme the first soviet gay and lesbian newspaper 
to protect identities the association keeps no formal 
membership roll activists said it has only 20 to 25 regular 
participants but many more supporters 
the first three issues of the newspaper distributed in 
february july and november contained articles on such topics as 
gay cinema homosexuality in russian history 
in a scathing article printed by leading newspapers nov 15 the 
government tass news agency accused the group of harboring not only 
primitive homosexuals but necrophiliacs pedophiles and 
zoophiles 
where can you find a fresh corpse to excite a necrophiliac 
how much does it cost to have sex with a baby why doesnt moscow 
have official places for men to entertain themselves with little 
boys and girls with girls for only two rubles tema provides its 
readers with the answers to these and other nasty questions tass 
said 
roman kalinin temas 24yearold editor denied the paper had 
published such information tass knew perfectly well it was 
untrue he said 
in addition to publishing tema the association of sexual 
minorities collects information on civil rights violations 
it reported in september that police and soldiers in the black 
sea resort of sochi raided a gay cafe and used billy clubs to force 
suspected homosexuals into a bus the men were driven to a 
hospital where doctors were ordered to test their blood for aids 
the association said 
activists said western gay and lesbian groups so far have 
contributed several typewriters a small amount of money under 
1000 and 7000 condoms to the association 
kalinin who spent november in the united states meeting with 
homosexual groups at the invitation of the usbased international 
gay and lesbian human rights commission said he believes more aid 
will be coming 
already he said international activists have planned a gay 
parade through red square for the summer of 1991 
