<TEXT>
toronto canadas new year is filled with problems the threat 
of separation by frenchspeaking quebec an increasingly volatile 
indian population and a deepening recession 
coping with it will be the most unpopular government since 
opinion polling began in canada half a century ago 
the latest polls say 58 percent of canadians rate prime minister 
brian mulroney who need not call an election for three years as 
the worst prime minister or one of the worst support for 
his progressive conservative party has sunk to 14 percent 
a commission created by the quebec legislature is holding 
hearings and will make recommendations in march on what steps to 
take after the failure of the meech lake constitutional accord in 
june that accord declared quebec a distinct society and 
provided for other constitutional changes sought by the province 
a recent poll shows 73 percent of french speakers in quebec 
favor sovereigntyassociation an illdefined form of partial 
independence from the central government 
an explosion of violence in two mohawk communities and a long 
