said friday it wont pay its shareholders a midyear dividend 
because of weak cash flow 
the owner of the usbased j walter thompson and ogilvy amp 
mather worldwide advertising agencies said its priority was to 
conserve cash 
wpp has grown into the largest ad and marketing group in the 
world through acquisitions over the past five years but has seen 
growth in its businesses slowed by the economic weakness in the 
united states and great britain 
we consider that it would not be in the best interests of the 
company to pay the interim dividend for 1990 and therefore this 
dividend will not be paid wpp said in a letter to shareholders 
the interim dividend was to have been for the six months ended 
june 30 and was to have been paid on jan 2 the company said in 
august it was going to pay a halfyear dividend of 137 pence or 
26 cents a share last year the interim dividend was 113 pence 
or 215 cents a share 
wpps decision to omit the dividend surprised analysts 
this underlines how difficult a position the company is 
in said an analyst at barclays de zoete wedd ltd who declined 
to be identified if it has to conserve cash to this extent its 
obviously pretty serious 
wpp also said it could be some time before the group can 
resume the pattern of growth in profits and earnings experienced up 
until a few months ago 
wpp reported a 77 percent rise in pretax profit to 46 million 
pounds or 87 million for the first six months of the year from 
26 million pounds in the same period a year earlier 
however the group warned in november that its fullyear pretax 
profit wouldnt match stockbrokers estimates of about 110 million 
pounds or 209 million 
the news prompted a 70 percent drop in the value of its stock 
over two days and fridays announcement ignited another decline 
the stock which had been trading at 392 pence before the 
november announcement was down another 14 pence on friday at 47 
pence on londons stock exchange 
some analysts say wpp may have trouble meeting its debts which 
they said totaled 320 million pounds or about 600 million 
barclays de zoete wedd is forecasting wpp will have a 1990 
pretax profit of 85 million pounds or 162 million wpps pretax 
profit came to 75 million pounds in 1989 
its 1989 profit after taxes was 405 million pounds or 77 
million on revenue of 44 billion pounds or 84 billion 
