driven newspapers to find alternate methods of generating more 
revenue 
in boosting prices the national said it was following the lead 
of national newspapers such as the wall street journal and the new 
york times which have recently either boosted or plan to raise 
prices 
the journal boosted its price per copy to 75 cents from 50 cents 
on dec 3 while the times plans to boost the price of its national 
edition to 75 cents from 50 cents in the midwes and from 60 cents 
in the southwest in january 
