<TEXT>
a higherthanexpected federal deficit tensions 
in the middle east and the holiday season combined to depress bond 
prices friday in moderate trading 
the treasurys bellwether 30year bond was down point or 
625 per 1000 in face amount at fridays closing its yield 
which rises when prices fall was up to 829 percent from 823 
percent late thursday 
we had more rhetoric coming from mideast situation the 
holiday atmosphere and a largerthanexpected budget deficit put 
it all together and i think it explains what happened today said 
kevin flanagan a money market economist for dean witter reynolds 
inc 
the federal government reported a 481 billion deficit in 
november a 62 percent increase over a year earlier the government 
blamed the red ink on the persian gulf buildup and a failing 
economy 
traders generally see large deficits as pushing up interest 
rates because the treasury must offer attractive yields when it 
peddles large amounts of debt to finance government operations 
iraqi president saddam hussein predicted in an interview 
broadcast friday that if war broke out in the gulf president bush 
would be forced to retreat after american casualties reached 5000 
saddam also refused to pull out of kuwait by the jan 15 
deadline set by the united nations for avoiding force traders 
predict a gulf war will hike the price of oil and increase 
inflation which erodes the price of bonds 
in addition the market faced what traders called yearend 
pressures because banks are scrambling to obtain cash and in turn 
bidding up the cost of funds to fulfill financial obligations 
before the new year 
broker marilyn cohen viewed the price drop as a normal 
pullback in a bull market for bonds people were so overbought in 
the bond market she said 
ms cohen investment broker for capital insight inc in beverly 
hills calif said she wasnt distressed over the decline in bond 
prices because clearly interest rates are not going up for the 
time being 
this is the relief the bond market needs in order to gather 
full steam and move ahead again she said 
in the secondary market for treasury bonds shortterm 
maturities were down 116 point to 732 point intermediate 
maturities fell point to 1332 point and longterm issues lost 
point to point the telerate inc financial information service 
reported 
the movement of a point is equivalent to a change of 10 in the 
price of a bond with a 1000 face value 
the lehman brothers daily treasury bond index which measures 
price movements on all outstanding treasury issues with maturities 
of a year or longer was down 291 to 118199 
yields on threemonth treasury bills held at 673 percent as the 
discount rate rose 1 basis point to 654 percent yields on 
sixmonth bills rose to 691 percent as the discount rose 6basis 
point to 660 percent yields on oneyear bills rose to 693 
percent as the discount was up 4 basis points to 651 percent 
a basis point is onehundredth of a percentage point the yield 
is the annualized return on an investment in a treasury bill the 
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face 
value paid at maturity 
the federal funds rate the interest on overnight loans between 
banks traded at 7 percent up from 7lsqb percent late thursday 
in the taxexempt market the bond buyer index of 40 actively 
traded municipal bonds dropped 132 point to 91 932 the average 
yield to maturity held at 747 from late thursday 
