<TEXT>
bank of new england corp would receive an 
injection of 605 million in capital if the ailing company agrees 
to a debtforequity swap proposed friday 
committees representing holders of 705 million worth of bank of 
new england bonds have agreed to exchange their bonds for stock 
that will give them 92 percent ownership of the company said 
wilbur ross who represents some of the bond holders 
meanwhile in washington the securities and exchange commission 
announced the troubled bank has settled without admitting or 
denying wrongdoing allegations that it didnt disclose financial 
problems in its quarterly financial statements 
settlement negotiations were reported earlier but neither the 
sec nor the bank would provide details until fridays announcement 
in washington 
under the debtforequity swap the debt would be reduced from 
705 million to 100 million the difference or 605 million 
would be converted to equity capital for the bank 
thats a huge amount ross said the bank severely needs 
capital 
but an analyst said this deal alone could not solve the banks 
problems 
gerard cassidy a bank analyst with tucker anthony inc called 
the deal a major step forward but i would not say this event in 
and by itself is a panacea for their problems 
he said the bank must reduce its troubled loan portfolio and 
hope that the economy will halt its slide and begin to rebound 
james dorsey a bank spokesman said the bank would review the 
bondholders offer and discuss it with the board of directors 
ross reading from a statement said the deal would provide the 
bank with additional flexibility and financial wherewithal to 
continue to address its current financial problems 
at the same time the finances would be saving the federal 
government enormous taxpayer sums which would otherwise be spent if 
the bank or its subsidiaries were to be closed 
bank of new england has struggled for more than a year from bad 
real estate loans analysts say the bank was hurt by a declining 
real estate market that exposed shoddy lending practices 
a congressional report released this week concluded that the 
bank became insolvent by some measures in june although the bank 
disputed the calculations 
at the end of its most recent quarter on sept 30 the bank had 
a capital to assets ratio of 11 percent below the 3 percent 
target set by federal regulators in orders signed by the government 
and the bank earlier this year 
the bank declined to say whether the capital infusion would push 
the ratio above that goal 
cassidy said it is uncertain whether the added capital would 
allow the bank to reach the 3 percent target noting that the bank 
is expected to report a fourthquarter loss 
under any proposed debtforequity swap the banks common 
shareholders will likely be wiped out the bank has said 
bank of new england shares were selling for 1 down 25 cents a 
share in late trading on the new york stock exchange 
in the sec action the federal stock market watchdog filed a 
civil lawsuit against the bank at federal court in washington 
charging the bank of new england knowingly understated losses in 
its loan portfolio in a quarterly financial report in september 
1989 
without admitting or denying the allegations the bank agreed to 
restate its third quarter financial statements for 1989 to have 
independent accountants review its internal auditing procedures and 
to otherwise reform its quarterly financial reporting practices 
were pleased we were able to arrive at a satisfactory 
settlement with the sec and that we can put this matter behind 
us said dorsey the bank spokesman the sec settlement has no 
affect on the companys current business operations and will in no 
way interfere with our ongoing affairs 
sec chairman richard c breeden said the agency did not seek 
monetary penalties from the bank because the allegations predated 
a 1990 law giving the sec powers to impose fines 
breeden said the banks second quarter financial statement in 
1989 didnt adequately address trends affecting the bank including 
the deteriorating new england real estate market in the third 
quarter it failed to contain adequate provisions for losses 
said breeden adding that the bank didnt take a 1 billion 
writeoff of its loan losses until after it made a 250 million 
public securities offering 
